Status report of Yi Tong Tse on 3/15/99

  The DPI simulation code works now for EchoStar, Harmonic Lightway and
  HITS bitstreams.  For HITS the splicing is non-seamless.

  I am currently in the processing of porting the simulation code to
  the C6x platform.  One problem I encountered is code size.  The combined
  code is about 90 KBytes.  The solution is to put non critical code in
  external memory, and use the large memory model to compile the code.
  The new version 2 C6x tools are used and a new version of the Kernel
  is also needed for the large memory model.

  Will try to run and debug the code in real hardware this week.


